title: ADVISORY - Jim Vena, CN executive vice-president and chief operating officer, to address Goldman Sachs Industrials Conference on Nov. 4
text:
CN
MONTREAL , Oct. 21, 2015 /PRNewswire/ - Jim Vena, executive vice-president and chief operating officer of CN (TSX: CNR) (NYSE: CNI), will address the Goldman Sachs Industrials Conference in Boston, Mass. , on Nov. 4, 2015 , starting at 8.40 a.m. Eastern Standard Time .
Vena will discuss CN's continuing focus on supply chain collaboration and Operational and Service Excellence.
CN will provide a live audio webcast of Vena's remarks via the Investors' section of its website, www.cn.ca/en/investors .
CN is a true backbone of the economy whose team of 25,000 railroaders transports more than C$250 billion worth of goods annually for a wide range of business sectors, ranging from resource products to manufactured products to consumer goods, across a rail network of approximately 20,000 route-miles spanning Canada and mid-America. CN – Canadian National Railway Company, along with its operating railway subsidiaries – serves the cities and ports of Vancouver , Prince Rupert, B.C. , Montreal , Halifax , New Orleans , and Mobile, Ala. , and the metropolitan areas of Toronto , Edmonton , Winnipeg , Calgary , Chicago , Memphis , Detroit , Duluth, Minn. / Superior, Wis. , and Jackson, Miss. , with connections to all points in North America . For more information about CN, visit the company's website at www.cn.ca .
